Rust Control Flow: if, while and for loop In this blog post, we will discuss about the control flow in Rust programming language, specifically if, while and for loop.
If Statement In Rust, if is a keyword that allows you to branch your code based on conditions.
let number = 7; if number &lt; 5 { println!(&#34;condition was true&#34;); } else { println!(&#34;condition was false&#34;); }
